chordpro:
{title: Be Thou My Vision}
{key: Eb}
{time: 3/4}
{tempo: 90}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[Eb]Be Thou my [Bb]Vision, O [Cm]Lord of my [Ab]heart;
[Eb]Naught be all [Bb]else to me, [Cm]save that Thou [Bb]art.
[Ab]Thou my best [Eb]Thought, by [Cm]day or by [Ab]night,
[Eb]Waking or [Bb]sleeping, Thy [Ab]presence my [Eb]light.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
[Eb]Be Thou my [Bb]Wisdom, and [Cm]Thou my true [Ab]Word;
[Eb]I ever with [Bb]Thee and [Cm]Thou with me, [Bb]Lord;
[Ab]Thou my great [Eb]Father, I [Cm]Thy true [Ab]son;
[Eb]Thou in me [Bb]dwelling, and [Ab]I with Thee [Eb]one.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
[Eb]Riches I [Bb]heed not, nor [Cm]man's empty [Ab]praise,
[Eb]Thou mine in[Bb]heritance, [Cm]now and [Bb]always:
[Ab]Thou and Thou [Eb]only, first [Cm]in my [Ab]heart,
[Eb]High King of [Bb]Heaven, my [Ab]Treasure Thou [Eb]art.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
[Eb]High King of [Bb]Heaven, my [Cm]victory [Ab]won,
[Eb]May I reach [Bb]Heaven's joys, O [Cm]bright Heaven's [Bb]Sun!
[Ab]Heart of my [Eb]own heart, what[Cm]ever be[Ab]fall,
[Eb]Still be my [Bb]Vision, O [Ab]Ruler of [Eb]all.
{end_of_verse}
